Governor Muhammad Badaru Abubakar of Jigawa state has formed a new cabinet with the swear-in of 11 Commissioners and 15 Special Advisers. Governor Badaru inaugurated his second term executive council at Government House conference in Dutse after 120 days in office. He called on the new appointees to support his administration in providing good governance to the citizens of the state. He said the reelection of APC in the state is a clear testimony that the people of the state have confidence on his administration. The newly appointed commissioners included; Abba Zakari Ministry of Health, Musa Adamu Aliyu, Ministry of Justice,
Ibrahim Baba Chaichai, Ministry of Environment. Others included, Muhammad Alhassan Ministry of Information Youth, Sport and Culture, Kabiru, Hassan Sugungun Ministry of Local Government, Babangida Umar Gantsa Ministry of Finance. Others were Lawan Yunusa Danzomo Ministry of Education, Yelwa Da’u Tijjani Ministry of Women Affairs, Salisu Zakari, Ministry for Commerce and Industries, Ibrahim Garba Hannun Giwa Ministry of Water Resources and Aminu Usman Ministry of Works and Housing. The Governor called on citizens of the state to support the newly appointed commissioners to discharge their responsibilities accordingly. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.